sentences.en: ‘The Express’ was the first paper to print the story.
sentences.cn: 《快报》是首家刊登这一事件的报纸。

sentences.en: books that are out of print.
sentences.cn: 已售完的书

sentences.en: books that are still in print.
sentences.cn: 这些书仍可买到

sentences.en: denials that were to be found in print.
sentences.cn: 以印刷形式出现的否认声明

sentences.en: First released in 1957, the movie now appears in a new print.
sentences.cn: 1957年首次上映后，这部影片现在有了新的拷贝。

sentences.en: Getting his book into print has been an Olympian task in itself.
sentences.cn: 将他的书付印本身就是一件浩大的工程。

sentences.en: He was praised in print and memorialized in stone throughout the South.
sentences.cn: 在整个南方地区，他被人们著书称颂，刻碑纪念。

sentences.en: I got a kick out of seeing my name in print.
sentences.cn: 当看到我的名字印成铅字时，我感到无比兴奋。

sentences.en: I paid a visit to my local print shop.
sentences.cn: 我去了我们当地的照片冲洗店.

sentences.en: I shall just print this out and put it in the post.
sentences.cn: 我只需把它打印出来，然后投进邮筒。

sentences.en: Laser printers give high quality print.
sentences.cn: 激光打印机的打印质量很好。

sentences.en: Many books that are out of print are reissued in paperback form.
sentences.cn: 许多绝版的书籍又以平装本形式重新出现.

sentences.en: Many of their books have been in print for nearly 40 years.
sentences.cn: 他们的很多书都印行将近40年了。

sentences.en: Many of these poets appeared in print only long after their deaths.
sentences.cn: 这些诗人中有很多都是在去世很久以后作品才得以发表的。

sentences.en: Over five million copies of the paper are printed every day.
sentences.cn: 这份报纸每日印量超过五百万。

sentences.en: Print your name and address on a postcard and send it to us.
sentences.cn: 中文例句: 用印刷体将你的名字和地址写在一张明信片上寄给我们。

sentences.en: Read all the small print before signing.
sentences.cn: 把小号字印刷的附加条款全部看过以后再签字。

sentences.en: The names were traced out in stark black print.
sentences.cn: 这些名字是用醒目的黑体字印出的.

sentences.en: the pleasure of seeing my name in print
sentences.cn: 在出版物中看到我名字时的那份喜悦

sentences.en: There was no print at all on the backs of the tickets.
sentences.cn: 门票背面没有印任何文字。

sentences.en: Very little of his poetry actually got into print (= was printed ) .
sentences.cn: 他的诗作鲜有付梓。

sentences.en: Wayne plans to increase the print run to 1,000.
sentences.cn: 韦恩打算将印量增加到1,000册。

sentences.en: When the book was first written no publisher would print it.
sentences.cn: 这本书刚写成时没有出版商愿意出版。

sentences.en: Will you print in the missing names for me?
sentences.cn: 你能替我把那些漏掉的名字添上 吗 ?

sentences.en: You have to type in commands, such as "help" and "print"
sentences.cn: 你必须输入命令,例如“帮助”或“打印”.

phrases.tran_cn: （契约中）难懂的条文；极小的字体
可买到的，仍在出售的：由出版商提供出售的
已售完的，已绝版的：不再被出版商提供出售的
列印：作为一项功能而打印；打印出
（协议等上面用小号字体写成的）附属细则
书面语言（尤指相对于口头表述）

trans.tran_cn: 印刷字体，印出的字，印记，出版界，印花织物，照片，电影拷贝，版画，脚印，指纹
trans.tran_en: writing that has been printed, for example in books or newspapers

trans.tran_cn: 打印，印刷，刊登，印染，冲洗，压印
trans.tran_en: to produce many printed copies of a book, newspaper etc
